text: Alsodes coppingeri is a frog. It lives in Chile and Argentina. ==Home== This frog lives in forests that are not very hot or very cold and on cold grassland with mountains all around. People see it in leafy plants, under rocks, and near streams. Scientists have seen the frog between 0 and 300 meters above sea level. This frog lives in at least one protected place: Bernardo O'Higgins National Park. ==Young== This frog hatches out of its egg as a tadpole, not a froglet. ==Danger== Scientists do not know if this frog is in danger of dying out. American mink that people brought from other parts of the world can kill this frog. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Alsodes coppingeri
